observations.recommendation:
We have recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

Require the Inventory Committee to submit the Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Networks to the Office of the Auditor, using the prescribed format, within the prescribed period for timely verification and the reconciliation of the list of inventory per Local Road Inventory Report and Road Map with those recorded in the Road Networks account; 

Instruct the GSO to maintain Local Road Network Property Card to indicate the status and condition of each road networks and its components;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare Local Road Network Ledger Cards, and subsidiary records for each road networks and its components; and

Enjoin the concerned officials and employees to strictly comply to COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 23, 2015 to ensure fair presentation of the Local Road Network account in the Financial Statements.

We recommended that the Management:
Thru the Inventory Committee, submit the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment within the prescribed period, in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020, for the timely review and verification of the PPE accounts;
Update the property records based on the results of physical inventory, and reconcile the same with accounting records to make the records reflective of the actual count of PPEs;
Undertake all other procedures prescribed under COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 to come up with the reconciled and correct balances of PPE accounts in the financial statements;
Direct the GSO to maintain Property Cards and the Municipal Accountant to update the PPE Ledger Cards for each item of the PPE pursuant to Section 114, Paragraph 4 of the MNGAs for LGUs, Volume I; and
Direct the Municipal Accountant to accurately identify all the semi-expendable properties still recorded under the PPE accounts and draw the necessary journal entries to remove them from the books and close the related Accumulated Depreciation to the appropriate accounts.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
Require the Inventory Committee to submit the Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Networks to the Office of the Auditor, using the prescribed format, within the prescribed period for timely verification and the reconciliation of the list of inventory per Local Road Inventory Report and Road Map with those recorded in the Road Networks account;
Instruct the GSO to maintain Local Road Network Property Card to indicate the status and condition of each road network and its components;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare Local Road Network Ledger Cards, and subsidiary records for each road networks and its components and to provide adequate disclosure regarding the Road Network System in the Notes to Financial Statements using the format prescribed in COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 23, 2015; and
Enjoin the concerned officials and employees to strictly comply with COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 23, 2015 to ensure fair presentation of the Local Road Network account in the Financial Statements.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:
Coordinate with the Municipal Treasurer to confirm the status of the checks reported as outstanding to determine whether these were issued to the payees or cancelled checks;
Exert extra effort to review the long outstanding/stale checks and require the Municipal Treasurer to cancel the unclaimed stale checks and to furnish the Accounting Office with the original Disbursement Vouchers and its supporting documents, for the preparation of the Journal Entry Voucher, following the procedures prescribed to ensure recording of such cancellation;
Secure Monthly Bank Statements to prepare the Bank Reconciliation Statements to determine whether checks claimed by the payees were presented for payment, and secure the addresses of the payees for notification of the return of stale checks in their possession for replacement; and
Draw the JEV to restore the cash and liabilities pertaining to the stale checks to present fairly the recorded Cash in Bank and accounts payable accounts.

We recommended that the Management undertake the following:
Coordinate with the donor agencies and secure appropriate documents that will accurately provide the cost of these assets at the time of transfer, if possible.  Otherwise, the Management shall reliably determine their fair value at the time of acquisition;
Require the Municipal Accountant to record the costs in the books of the LGU using the appropriate PPE accounts and compute the corresponding accumulated depreciation;
Require the General Service Officer to bring the motorcycle for emission and submit its result in accordance with the instructions of the Provincial Government of Cagayan; and
Require the GSO to secure from the Provincial Government of Cagayan the copies of Deeds of Donation for the Patient Transport Vehicle and motorcycle.  Thereafter, appropriate procedures should be undertaken to transfer the Official Receipts and Certificates of Registration of the vehicles in the name of the LGU.

