We have recommended that the Management instruct the Municipal Accountant to:

Require the concerned barangays to submit immediately the liquidation reports for the previous years’ and current year’s fund transfers amounting to P556,680.61 and P6,049,550.91, respectively;

Continue the strict monitoring of the submission of liquidation reports and the issuance of demand letters to concerned barangays who failed to comply therewith. This will ensure immediate submission of liquidation reports after the purpose/s for which it was granted has been served or completed;

Prohibit the payment of fund transfer unless the required certification that previous fund transfers have already been liquidated or accounted for, thus avoiding accumulation of past due accounts pursuant to Item 3.1.1 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012; and

Initiate the request for write-off of the unaccounted balance amounting to P164,363.78 of the Due from LGUs account in accordance with COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016.

We have recommended that the Management:

Make a strategic action plan on the proper scheduling in the implementation of the projects /programs to ensure its full implementation, as well as utilize the funds budgeted thereon;

Review whether or not the prior years’ unimplemented projects are still appropriate for the needs of the constituents;

Direct the concerned department to monitor regularly the implementation of the 20% Development Plan and closely coordinate with other departments to fully achieve the desired goals and benefits as planned; and

Review the unexpended balances of appropriation of all completed PPAs for inclusion in the next budgeting period to finance projects under the 20% DF for the succeeding year.

