We recommended that Management install and maintain a system of internal control for the procurement, recording and monitoring of Supplies and Property, Plant and Equipment to ensure maximum and efficient utilization of government resources and to prevent or forestall manipulation and commission of irregularities, as follows:

• The procured items be received, accepted and recorded in the Stock or Property Cards by the Supplies/Property Officer. Stock Cards and Property Cards be maintained for each type of Supplies or PPE, respectively.; 

• The Supply/Property Officer issues supplies/PPE to the requesting office or end-users. The issuances should be supported with Requisition and Issue Slips. The issuance of small items not to be considered as PPE be covered with Inventory Custodian Slips (ICS) and issued PPE be supported with Acknowledgment Receipt for Equipment (ARE).;

• The Accounting Office should also maintain Supplies Ledger Cards and PPE Ledger Cards for supplies and PPE, respectively.; and

• The Supply/Property Office and Accounting Office reconcile their respective records regularly.
• If warranted, the municipality should put up a stockroom for safekeeping of the procured supplies and materials until issuance to the proper users, as may be needed thereby ensure economy and efficiency in the use of supplies and PPE of the Municipality.

